final_report.recommendation:
## Severity
MEDIUM

## Vulnerability Summary
The contract contains a potential Denial of Service (DoS) vulnerability within loops where the iteration condition relies on a dynamic array length (`candidates.length`). If an external call or state change modifies the array during execution, the loop condition may never terminate correctly, leading to excessive gas consumption and potential transaction failure.

## Exploit Pattern
An attacker can exploit this by manipulating the contract state (e.g., pushing new elements into the array) concurrently with a function execution that iterates over it. This forces the loop to re-evaluate an ever-increasing condition, causing the execution to consume excessive gas until the block limit is hit or the transaction reverts due to running out of gas.

## Recommended Fix
Ensure that loop conditions use a cached value for length checks before iteration begins. Instead of `for (int i = 0; i < candidates.length; i++)`, cache the length:

```solidity
// Example fix structure:
uint256 length = candidates.length;
for (uint256 i = 0; i < length; i++) {
    // ... operations
}
```

> **NOTE:** Contract exceeded 512 CodeBERT tokens — tail code was not analysed. Manual review of the unanalysed portion is recommended.

